race.description: Celebrating The Life Of Jason Oliver Maiden
race.comment: SOUTHERN FIRETAIL (5) was a beaten favourite on debut at Ascot in a far stronger field, and even from a wide gate, he is the one to beat at this level, especially with William Pike retaining the ride. On top for us. HOPE TO ADMIRE (4) has been thereabouts in all of his 3 starts back from a spell, and he is another who will appreciate racing at country-class level. A wide gate is no help, but he can run in the top 3 here. SEA OF GALILEE (2) has struck form since racing on this track, and he has been runner-up in his last couple of starts. Each way claims again. MAID AN OFFER (1) finished fifth as the favourite in a 7-horse field when having his first start from the local Indianna Weinert stable. He will be better for it, and is worth another chance. Follow your money. CAPRICIOUS RULER (9) was a shade disappointing in 2 starts from the powerful Williams stable, and ran a better race last time out for Roy Rogers when finishing fourth. She can continue to improve. Include in all combos.
